<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[264,1323,284,710]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,452,644,670]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
Generic name is a combination of the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1018,1145,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">byssoideus</emphasis>
(filiform) and 
<emphasis box="[264,327,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">cerus</emphasis>
(antenna), because the third and fourth antennal segments are very thin.
</paragraph>
